ZCZC GE23
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 102300 UTC
THROUGH FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY A FAIRLY DEEP AREA OF
LOW PRESSURE 983 MBAR WILL BE CENTRED TO THE W OF
FITZROY. THE SCANDINAVIAN HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM WILL
EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE N SEA AND UK. PRESSURE WILL BE
LOW ACROSS THE MEDITERRANEAN SEA AND NEAR ICELAND. A
SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH SUNDAY AND
MONDAY ALTHOUGH THE RIDGE AXIS WILL LIKELY DRIFT SLWY
NWARDS ALLOWING A TIGHTER PRESSURE GRADIENT TO FORM OVER
THE SERN N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL. ON FRIDAY EVENING AND
SATURDAY WINDS WILL BE MAINLY LIGHT OR MOD IN THE
CULLERCOATS REGION BUT NE FRESH AT TIMES IN THE S AND
POSSIBLY OCNL STRG IN THE DOVER STRAIT. NE WINDS MAY
CONTINUE TO BE OCNL STRG IN THE DOVER STRAIT ON SUNDAY
AND PERHAPS LATER IN FISHER AND GERMAN BIGHT. ON MONDAY
STRG NE WINDS MAY DEVELOP IN FORTIES AND FISHER AND IN
SEA AREAS FURTHER S
